  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lank shares gains in mid-day trade",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s shares gained 0.91% in mid-morning trade on Friday (02).",
        "The main All Share Price Index gained 84.38 points to 9,339.19 at 1145 hours.",
        "The market gained on Thursday upon the IMF announcement of giving a\u00a04-year 2.9 billion US dollar extended fund facility subject to debt restructuring and prior actions to Sri Lanka.",
        "Under the program, the budget will have to generate a primary surplus (debt before interest) of 2.3 percent.",
        "Most liquid index gained 0.59 percent or 17.61 points to 3,022.93.",
        "Top gainers were LOLC Holdings, LOLC Finance and Browns Investments. (Colombo/Sep02/2022)"
      ],
